         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><note>1</note> When emperor Caesar Trajan Hadrian Augustus, son of deified Trajan, victor in Parthia, grandson of deified Nerva, was <supplied reason="lost">chief priest</supplied>, 
               holding tribunician <supplied reason="lost">power</supplied> for the eleventh time, <supplied reason="lost">consul for the third, father</supplied> of the country 
               <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> </p><p><note>2.a.</note><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>b.<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">Publius</supplied> Valerius Priscus proconsul, employing Popilius Celer his legate <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></p><p>c. ? took the auspices <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> baths <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> d.<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> public<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> j.<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Lepcitanian <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></p><p>The other fragments are not usefully translatable.</p></div>
